TITLE: Boeing's last 747 has rolled out of the factory after a more than 50-year production run
SUMMARY: Boeing has produced 1,574 of the planes at its factory north of Seattle.

TITLE: Billionaire investor Charlie Munger: ‘The world is not driven by greed, it’s driven by envy’
SUMMARY: The 98-year-old billionaire says he's 'conquered envy.' In the past, he's said that's a secret to a long and happy life.

TITLE: Crypto.com CEO has history of red flags including bankruptcy and quick exits
SUMMARY: Before Crypto.com, Kris Marszalek left behind a trail of personal bankruptcy, offshore payments, and a corporate collapse that separated users from their funds.

TITLE: Cramer’s week ahead: Don’t let the Fed’s meeting obscure investing opportunities
SUMMARY: Two key economic events take place next week, including the release of the November consumer price index report and the Federal Reserve’s December meeting.

TITLE: China, Saudi Arabia stress importance of oil market stability as Xi visits Riyadh
SUMMARY: China and Saudi Arabia stressed the importance of oil market stability during President Xi Jinping's three-day visit to the Mideast Gulf kingdom.

TITLE: TSMC bucks broader chip slump with 50% revenue surge, helped by Apple iPhone orders
SUMMARY: The world's largest contract chipmaker reported the November surge thanks in part to orders of semiconductors for high-end smartphones such as Apple's iPhone.

TITLE: Harry and Meghan hit out at 'exploitation and bribery' of UK media in new Netflix documentary
SUMMARY: Prince Harry and Meghan Markle hit out at what they called the "exploitation and bribery" of the British press in a new Netflix documentary released Thursday.

TITLE: A nutritionist shares the 'underrated' longevity food she eats every day to boost her immune system
SUMMARY: Want to live to 100? Research says eating more legumes could help you live a longer life. Nutritionist Samantha Heller shares the benefits of this unexpectedly versatile food.

TITLE: Huawei licenses 5G patents to rival as U.S. sanctions force the Chinese giant to seek new revenue
SUMMARY: Huawei historically has not monetized its huge chest of 5G patents but it is looking to find new revenue streams after U.S. sanctions crushed its mobile business.

TITLE: Majority of Americans don't want Biden or Trump to run again in 2024, CNBC survey shows
SUMMARY: The survey found 61% of the public think Trump should not seek the presidency, compared with 30% who believe he should.

TITLE: Southeast Asia's 5G outlook remains 'bleak' in short term despite tech giant partnership, report says
SUMMARY: A report by Fitch Solutions says that a 5G partnership between two conglomerates could help accelerate 5G in Southeast Asia but the outlook remains "bleak."

TITLE: China's yuan could get a boost as Covid measures ease, says BK Asset Management
SUMMARY: The onshore and offshore Chinese yuan is expected to strengthen even further than current levels, according to BK Asset Management.

TITLE: UK announces major overhaul of its financial sector in attempt to spur growth
SUMMARY: The U.K. government is seeking to overhaul EU laws that "choke off growth."

TITLE: Brits told to rethink Christmas plans with strikes set to hit flights and train travel
SUMMARY: The government has urged the public to rethink their travel plans if they are on an affected service.

TITLE: Bahamas attorneys file emergency motion in FTX case for access to databases with client information
SUMMARY: Lawyers for Bahamian regulators asked a judge in Delaware bankruptcy court to allow them access to FTX data so they can locate assets and information.

TITLE: Taylor Swift signs on to direct a movie for Disney as she campaigns for short film Oscar
SUMMARY: Taylor Swift has written an original script that will be produced by Disney's Searchlight Pictures.

TITLE: What to expect next as China relaxes Covid controls
SUMMARY: As mainland China relaxes many of its stringent Covid controls, analysts point out the country is far from a quick return to a pre-pandemic situation.

TITLE: Europe’s energy grids face first major winter stress test as Arctic blast takes hold
SUMMARY: Temperatures across the Nordic countries and central and eastern Europe are also set to drop to close to or below freezing over the coming days.

TITLE: European Central Bank warns that an EU gas price cap risks financial stability
SUMMARY: The European Central Bank warned that an EU-wide cap on natural gas prices could jeopardize financial stability in the region.

TITLE: Americans are flocking to wildfire country
SUMMARY: From 2010 to 2020, Americans migrated to the Pacific Northwest, Southwest, Texas, Florida, and parts of the Southeast. Many of these places are prone to fire.

SUMMARY: Russia and Ukraine are sending out smoke signals that there is no time — and no desire — for a cessation of hostilities.

SUMMARY: Donald Trump, who is again running for the White House, is under criminal investigation for the removal of government documents when his presidency ended.

TITLE: Grocery delivery firm Getir acquires embattled rival Gorillas as industry consolidates
SUMMARY: The long-rumored takeover reportedly values Gorillas at $1.2 billion, down 15% from its last valuation.

TITLE: UK's new finance reforms part of a 20-year plan to be 'world's next Silicon Valley,' minister says
SUMMARY: The reforms have been touted as a post-Brexit overhaul of EU laws that "choke off growth."

TITLE: CNBC Stock World Cup 2022: Recap of winners and losers so far
SUMMARY: If you invest today, which of the two companies going head to head will give you a greater total return over the next 12 months? We ask experts.

TITLE: Apple supplier Foxconn reportedly helped persuade China to loosen Covid rules
SUMMARY: Foxconn founder Terry Gou reportedly said China's zero-Covid policy threatened its position in global supply chains.

TITLE: Arizona Sen. Kyrsten Sinema leaves Democratic Party to become independent
SUMMARY: Sinema said in a tweet she was declaring her "independence from the broken partisan system in Washington and formally registering as an Arizona Independent."

TITLE: Turkey is stopping oil not under Russian sanctions, raising global energy market supply concerns
SUMMARY: Much of the oil being held up by Turkey is Kazakh-origin and not subject to a Russian crude price cap, but shipment delays may impact the global energy market.

TITLE: Tech layoffs in Southeast Asia mount as unprofitable startups seek to extend their runways
SUMMARY: Tech layoffs have been increasing in Southeast Asia as growth slows down. Existing investors are also pushing startups to extend their runways.

TITLE: FTX spokesman Kevin O'Leary says he lost his $15 million payday from crypto firm
SUMMARY: Kevin O'Leary made millions as an FTX spokesman, but he says he's lost it all after the bankruptcy of the crypto exchange.
